
[1]mite

   MITE, n. [Heb. small.]

   1. A very small insect of the genus Acarus.

   2. In Scripture, a small piece of money, the quarter of a denarius, or
   about seven English farthings.

   3. Any thing proverbially very small; a very little particle or
   quantity.

   4. The twentieth part of a grain.
